Private API Gateway with the AWS CDK
1. Lambda
2. Private Api Gateway
3. VPC Endpoint
NB: In order to access the Api Gateway through the public DNS of the VPC endpoint, a curl request has to have the api id as header. See also here

Test
Create a EC2 in the public subnet
curl -i -H "x-apigw-api-id: <api-id>" https://vpce-<vpce-id>.execute-api.<region>.vpce.amazonaws.com/

SUCCESS Example:
curl -i -H "x-apigw-api-id: fgl4cf6765" https://vpce-097468dae72b0bb67.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod/
OR
curl https://fgl4cf6765-vpce-097468dae72b0bb67.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/prod/